63-67 Amongst Laterensis' claims to public favour, Cassius has

⁴ mentioned that he gave games at Praeneste ; but that was the usual thing for a quaestor to do. If, however, emphasis is laid on the fact that at Cyrene Laterensis behaved with great liberality and fairness towards the publicani and others, the jury should remember how little is known in Rome of provincial affairs. Of this Cicero cites an instance from his own public life, at the same time showing how his experience taught him a lesson which Laterensis ought to have learned too -that to attain to office he must do his utmost to gain popularity at Rome.
